  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Early livelihoods recovery of families at high risk affected by Hurricane ETA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A total of 350.3 thousand hectares of damaged or lost crops in Honduras -Nicaragua will devastate rural livelihoods, while forecast rains in Guatemala may bring irreparable damages to staple crops, threatening a rapid deterioration of the food security situation and a spike in malnutrition among vulnerable children in the three countries.
- 160 households (1005 people) have food in the immediate post-Hurricane stage and are early recovering food and nutritional security.
- Two departments (2,000people) will receive awareness campaigns on good hygiene prevention practices (through the radio and the local periphery) to promote measures against the transmission of Covid19, health practices and waterborne diseases aggravated by the floods; and protection messages to ensure adequate care for children and the elderly.
- Diagnosis of vulnerabilities, damages and needs for long-term rehabilitation at the local level where there is a presence</narrative>
  </description>
